      "message": "A lot of our older iterators use this bool next() or Foo* next() pattern but many of the newer ones are designed to be used with range for loops, which I find much nicer.  To do that you\u0027d have to do something like make a ContourRange type that defines a begin() and end() that return an iterator so you could write something like:\n\nfor (auto\u0026 countor : SkPathPriv::ContourRange(path)) {\n    for (int i \u003d 0; i \u003c contour.countVerbs(); ++i) {\n...\n    }\n}",
